* GNU C-Graph 2.0.1
  New features:
	Update to use latest Autotools versions.
	Prepend "c-graph-" to Texinfo image filenames for
	coexistence with other Texinfo files in system-wide
	info directory.
  

* GNU C-Graph 2.0 
  Reproduction of 1983 dissertation released as GNU C-Graph May 2011.
  New features:
  	Pulses corresponding to each periodic signal, sawtooth wave,
	default values for unexpected user input, error handling, 
	scaling. Gnuplot for visualization.

* C-Graph 1.0 
  Model in C of the 5 core subroutines from 1983
  dissertation, presented November 1997 to the University of Aberdeen
  as evidence of authorship:
  	Periodic signals - triangle, rectangle, sine, cosine,
	Linear convolution.

* "Interactive Computer Package Demonstrating: Sampling Convolution
  and the FFT" BSc. Honours dissertation, University of Aberdeen,
  1983. The package was coded in Fortran 77 on the University's
  Honeywell mainframe:
  	Periodic signals - triangle, rectangle, sine, cosine.
	Aperiodic signals - exponential, step, ramp.
	Linear and circular convolution.
  	      

